    <h2>When Not to Use Iceberg</h2>

    <p>
      Iceberg is designed for large analytical tables. It adds overhead that is
      not worth it for small reference tables with a few thousand rows (use a
      regular database). It is also not a good fit when you need sub-millisecond
      point lookups by primary key (use a transactional database or key-value
      store). And if all your compute runs inside a single managed warehouse
      that already handles table management, adding Iceberg may create more
      complexity than value.
    </p>

